Doc: Scope

This standard specifies terms and definitions, technical requirements, test methods and requirements, appearance and identification, type inspection, manual and effective date of event data recorder of category M1 vehicles.
This standard applies for vehicles of category M1 installed with event data recorder.
Other vehicles could take it as reference.

For dated references, only the edition cited applies.
For undated references, the latest edition of the referenced document (including any amendments) applies.

Terms and Definitions For the purpose of this document, the terms and definitions given in <Regulation_GB14166> and following terms and definitions apply.
Impact event Means the impact or other physical event that causes the trigger threshold to be met or exceeded, or any other event which cuases non-reversible restraint is deployed
, whichever occurs first.

Event data recorder system (EDR) Means a device or system composed with one or more onboard electronic modules, and with data function of monitoring, collecting and recording vehicle and occupant protection system, prior to, during and after the event.
EDR controller Means an onboard electronic module used for monitoring, collecting and record of time series data in impact event occurrence process.
Lateral acceleration Means the component of the acceleration vector of a point in the vehicle in the Y-direction.
For Reference Purposes
Only Figure 1 Coordinate system of the vehicle
Longitudinal acceleration Means the component of the acceleration vector of a point in the vehicle in the X-axis direction.
The longitudinal acceleration is positive in the direction of forward vehicle travel, see Figure 1.
Normal acceleration Means the component of the vector acceleration of a point in the vehicle in the Z-axis direction.
The normal acceleration is positive in a downward direction, see Figure 1.
Delta-V Means the vector difference between pre-impact vehicle velocity and post-impact vehicle velocity.

EDR record Means the time series data stored in one or more ECU specially recording EDR data after the occurrence of impact.
Trigger threshold Means the conditions meeting the requirements for EDR record.
Locked event Means the event for EDR record that meets locking conditions and cannot be overridden by subsequent events.
Unlocked event Means the event which EDR record may be overwritten by subsequent events if not meeting locking conditions.
Time zero (T0) Means the beginning of time point for an impact event defined in EDR system.
Protection system Means the interior fittings and devices intended to restrain the occupants.
[<Regulation_GB11551-2014>, definition 3.1]
Occupant protection control algorithm Means the impact sensing logic that activates occupant protection devices as necessary, not a pre-impact sensing logic.
Non-reversible restraint Means the restraint device that cannot be recovered to reuse condition through automatic recovery or manual adjustment.
Translating Means that EDR data retrieval tools convert data stored in an EDR record and render it into a human-readable report.

EDR data retrieval tool Means an electronic tool consisting of the hardware and software which meets below 8 For Reference Purposes Only functions and is used for read EDR record data: -- Make a connection to the vehicles connector meeting requirements defined in <Regulation_GBT 34589>-2017 Road vehicles -- Diagnostic connector; --

Read the EDR record data; -- Authenticate and save the un-translated binary EDR record to a file on a PC; -- Open and authenticate a saved, un-translated file(s) containing an EDR record(s) and translate it into a human-readable report.
EDR record retrieval Means the procedure that EDR data retrieval tool reads and translates EDR record and output report.
EDR record report Means the human-readable report containing the vehicle EDR record translated and outputed by the EDR data retrieval tool.
Upper control limits (UCL) Used to define the upper limit for compliance testing of a variable.
Lower control limits (LCL) Used to define the lower limit for compliance testing of a variable.
Technical Requirements
Impact event requirements
Trigger threshold
When vehicle reaches the following trigger threshold conditions, the event shall be recorded: -- -V, longitudinal only
, trigger threshold means a change in vehicle velocity in the X-axis direction that is not less than 8km/h within a 150ms interval.
-- - also, trigger threshold means a change in vehicle velocity in either the X-axis or Y-axis
direction that is not less than 8km/h within a 150ms interval.
When the manufacturer sets other trigger thresholds, the requirements <Paragraph_4.1.1.1> <Paragraph_4.1.1.2> shall also be met.
Locking conditions

EDR shall choose either of the following as the locking condition, and the event data shall not be overridden: -- Non-reversible restraint deployment; -- The vehicle velocity change in X-axis direction is not less than 25km/h within 150ms interval.
In case of occurrence of rear-impact, it is permitted to adopt the locking condition of the control algorithm at discretion of the manufacturer as locking condition.
In case of lateral impact, it is necessary to take deployment of lateral non-reversible restraint as locking condition.
If vehicle is not configured with lateral non-reversible restraint, vehicle manufacturer shall determine whether to lock.
If the manufacturer sets other locking conditions, the requirements <Paragraph_4.1.2.1> <Paragraph_4.1.2.2> shall also be met.

Duration of impact event
The duration of an impact event is the time interval between the beginning of an impact event (T0) and the end of the impact event (Tend).
Note:
The duration of an impact event may exceed the time recording capability of the EDR.

In impact event, data elements recorded by EDR shall meet the requirements in Annex A, and the EDR record data shall meet the test requirements <Paragraph_5.1>, 5.2 <Paragraph_5.3>.
For event data recording, only one event could process at any designated time.
EDR record function requirements
Storage medium requirements EDR data shall be recorded in non-volatile storage medium.
EDR trigger requirements When vehicle reaches the trigger threshold specified <Paragraph_4.1.1>, EDR controller shall 16 For Reference Purposes
Only trigger the recording of data, and meet the test requirements after test <Paragraph_5.3.2>.
Requirements on number of storage events EDR system shall be able to record at least continously three times of impact event data, and meet the test requirements after test <Paragraph_5.3.3>.
Requirements on storage coverage mechanism
If no further space is available for EDR to record an event, the unlocked event data shall be overridden by the current event data in turn as per time sequence.
But locked event data shall not be covered by subsequent event data.
Perform test as per 5.3.4, test requirements shall be met.
If manufacturer is allowed to set other storage coverage mechanisms, those shall meet requirements <Paragraph_4.3.4.1> as well.

Requirements on power-off storage In case of occurrence of impact event, if power supply circuit of the vehicle cannot supply power normally, EDR system itself shall feature power supply capability, it shall meet that under impact at single direction, all related ignition circuits fully deploy after power-off (150±10) ms (if available), EDR system shall record all data before T0 and data from T0 to power off (150±10) ms and test requirments <Paragraph_5.3.5> shall be met.
Requirements on data retrieval
General requirements After event, data recorded by EDR shall be retrieved and be protected from tampering or deletion.

Data retrieval symbols requirements

Retrieval data based on Controller Area Network (CAN) EDR data retrieval symbols based on Controller Area Network (CAN) shall be in conformity with the requirements in Annex B.1, assign an event identifier to each of the stored event, which shall be 0xFA13, 0xFA14 and 0xFA15 respectively.
Where, 0xFA13 is the identifier for the most recent event, 0xFA14 is the identifier for the second event from the bottom, 0xFA15 is identifier for the third event from the bottom.

: 0XFA10 is identifier for the public data, and 0XFA21, 0XFA31 and 0XFA41 are the identifiers for the most recent event, 0XFA22, 0XFA32 and 0XFA42 are the identifiers for the second event from the bottom, 0XFA23, 0XFA33 and 0XFA43 are identifiers for the third event from the bottom.
Data translating requirements
The data recorded by EDR shall comply with the requirements of Table A.1 of Annex A and shall be translated according to the data arrangement of Table B.1 in Annex B.
Storage time limit requirements
If the EDR storage unit has not been replaced, the event data stored by EDR system shall be readable in the entire life cycle of the vehicle.
Other data retrieval requirements If the EDR data is dispersed and stored in different onboard electronic modules, the time synchronization of recorded data shall be guaranteed.

Electromagnetic compatibility requirements The vehicle equipped with EDR system shall comply with the requirements of <Regulation_GB34660>.
Test Methods and Requirements
Impact test
Before test, horizontal or longtigudinal acceleration sensor of the vehicle shall be installed in or near the longitudinal center plane of the vehicle by test chamber.

If the EDR controller to which vehicle acceleration sensor belongs is within this plane, the acceleration sensor for test chamber shall be installed on the surface or in adjacency 21 For Reference Purposes Only of the EDR controller, the distance between sensor and the controller surface shall be less than 30mm; otherwise, the the acceleration sensor for test chamber shall be installed on rigid fixture part surface in occupant compartment, and shall be in front of lateral plane of R-and the distance between sensor and the controller surface shall be less than 30mm.

Vehicle equipped with frontal airbag shall be tested in accordance with the requirements of <Regulation_GB11551-2014> or <Regulation_GBT 20913>, and make record of the deployment time of non-reversible restraint equipped for vehicle.
Vehicle equipped with side airbag shall be tested in accordance with the requirements of <Regulation_GB20071>, and make record of the deployment time of non-reversible restraint equipped for vehicle.
Vehicle unequipped with frontal airbag, side airbag or side air curtain shall be tested in accordance with the requirements of <Regulation_GB11551-2014> or <Regulation_GBT 20913>.

After the test, the EDR data shall be saved in the format of Annex A and read by the EDR data retrieval tool, and the read data shall meet the following requirements: -- The acquired delta-V or acceleration data shall meet the conformity requirements of delta-V curve in Annex D, and delta-V data shall not produce clipping, or acceleration data shall not exceed range of acceleration sensor; -- EDR system shall completely record all data required in Annex A.
Driving operation data test

In test, engine of the vehicle is at operation status (battery electric vehicles or hybrid electric vehicles are at power-on status), vehicle electronic/electric system recorded by EDR shall maintain operation status, relevant parts shall be configured as follows at least: -- Brake pedal and accelerator pedal shall maintain certain travel, and shall avoid empty travel position; -- Steering wheel shall be fixed at certain angle, and shall avoid empty travel position; -- Safety belt buckle shall be under locked status; -- Lamp required to be recorded shall be under ON status.

Impact threshold can be triggered by adopting but not limited to four methods as follows in test: 22 For Reference Purposes Only -- Impact vehicle in such a way that vehicle reaches trigger threshold; -- Fix vehicle on trolley and impact trolley in such a way that vehicle reaches trigger threshold; --
Physically trigger EDR system of the vehicle in such a way that vehicle reaches trigger threshold; --
Input the trigger signal to EDR system of the vehicle in such a way that vehicle reaches trigger threshold.
The EDR system shall be triggered and data shall be recorded, and the data shall meet the recording requirements
<Paragraph_4.2>.
Meanwhile, record of relevant data shall be identical with configuration <Paragraph_5.2.1>.
Bench test
Test preparation

Manufacturer shall provide test box used for connecting with EDR controller, this test box used for simulating peripheral signal and load in in actual vehicle status to EDR controller, shall meet below requirements: -- Test box shall have bus signals simulation function, simulating actual vehicle net information and send to EDR controller; -- Test box shall have necessary peripheral sensor, load and hardware connection parts connected with EDR controller, to guarantee the normal work of EDR controller; --
The power supply for EDR controller test shall be provided by the test bench (impact bench) rather than the test box.
EDR controller and its accessories are installed on impact bench as connection status with real vehicles, connected with test box, and supplied power via test bench.
The simulation signal and load provided by test chamber shall be preset and confirmed.
The device that is in operation during vehicle operation and is triggered to operate under certain arithmetic logic shall be preset as activated.
EDR system trigger test
The storage space of the EDR controller before the test shall ensure that valid data can be recorded.

Apply acceleration in accordance with impact waveform in Annex D.1 to longitudinal 23 For Reference Purposes Only direction of EDR controller through test bench (impact bench), and acquire the longitudinal acceleration through test chamber acceleration sensor.
EDR controller shall trigger work, its record data shall be identical with preset data <Paragraph_5.3.1.3>.
Test of number of storage events
Prior to test, EDR controller storage space shall be able to record at least 3 complete events.

Apply acceleration in accordance with any impact waveform in Annex D to longitudinal direction of EDR controller through impact bench, and acquire the acceleration through test chamber acceleration sensor.
Perform at least 3 impact tests as per the requirements <Paragraph_5.3.2.2>, with each test interval more than 5s.

EDR controller shall trigger work, and shall record data of latest consecutive 3 times of events, its data shall be is identical with pre-set data <Paragraph_5.3.1.3>, and EDR controller shall be newly added with data record for at least 3 times of events.
Storage coverage mechanism test
Unlocked event coverage test
Prior to test, EDR controller shall have no sufficient storage space for recording a complete event, and there is at least one unlocked event in the last three events stored.

Apply acceleration in accordance with impact waveform in Annex D.1 to longitudinal direction of EDR controller through test bench (impact bench), and acquire the acceleration through test chamber acceleration sensor.
EDR controller shall trigger work, EDR record data override the existing unlocked event data, and its record data shall be identical with preset data <Paragraph_5.3.1.4>.
Locked event coverage test
Prior to test, EDR controller shall have no sufficient storage space for recording a complete event, and there is fullly unlocked event in the stored events.

Apply acceleration in accordance with corresponding locking impact waveform in Figure D.2 to longitudinal direction of EDR controller through test bench (impact bench), and acquire the acceleration through test chamber acceleration sensor.
For Reference Purposes Only
The data record of the EDR controller is consistent with that before the test.
Power-off storage test
Prior to test, EDR controller storage space shall be able to record at least 1 event.

Apply acceleration in accordance with breaking impact waveform in Figure D.3 to longitudinal direction of EDR controller through test bench (impact bench), and acceleration through test chamber acceleration sensor.
At the same time of application of impact waveform, disconnect power supply to EDR controller.
EDR controller shall trigger work, its record data shall be identical with preset data <Paragraph_5.3.1.4>.
Appearance and Identification Vehicle manufacturer information and controller manufacturer information

(allow to mark abbreviation or logo), specification and model, and unique number of ECU recording EDR data shall be marked on surface of EDR controller, by means of nameplate, label, punching or mould, logo is clear and easy to see, durable and difficult to replace.
Type Inspection
General For vehicle models that have passed type inspection as per this standard, the results can be expanded to other vehicle models conforming to the determination condition <Paragraph_7.2>.
After vehicle model is granted with expansion, the expansion vehicle model shall not be expanded further to other vehicle models.
Determinant condition
Complete vehicle manufacturer is identical.
EDR controller manufacturer is identical.
EDR controller model is identical.
For complete vehicle impact test, the following conditions are included too: a)
The length of the vehicle portion in front of lateral plane passing R-point of b)
The arrangement of EDR controller on complete vehicle is identical.
For Reference Purposes
Only c) Model, accuracy and arrangement of EDR acceleration sensor are identical.
d)
The arrangement and configuration of the non-reversible restraint such as vehicle airbags and pretensioning seat belts related to the direction of impact are identical or its quantity decreases.
e)
EDR software version number shall be identical, but it could be modified with the exception of the situation that its change does not influence airbag control strategy and EDR storage strategy.
Note:
Airbag control strategy includes continuous/wakeup algorimoth, airbag quantity, location and quanity of sensor related to airbag deployment.

For drive operation test, the following conditions are included too: Data resource and transmission strategy of isuch as brake, acceleration, steering signal (refers to data sources such as buses or hardwires, sensors, etc.) are identical.
For bench test, difference of software version number is permitted, the following conditions are included too:
a) Edata is identical or is decreased, the acquisition mode (refers to data sources such as buses or hardwires, sensors, etc.)
shall be identical.
b)
The arrangement and configuration of the non-reversible restraint such as airbags and pretensioning seat belts related to the direction of impact are identical or its quantity decreases.
c)
Storage strategy is identical (lock, override, concentrated or distributed), number of storages, storage controller and model and storage medium shall be identical.
d)
The range and accuracy of sensor from which EDR acquires acceleration are equivalent or higher.
e)
The energy storage capacitor of EDR storage unit is equivalent or increased (only applicable to power-off storage test).

Manual For vehicles fitted with EDR, its product manual shall at least include: a) Declaration such as this vehicle is fitted with EDR; b) Explanation for meaning and possible purpose of EDR record data item; 26 For Reference Purposes

Only c) Explanation for supplier and accessible way for EDR data retrieval tool; d) Way of retrieval data from EDR controller; e) Explanation for data source of the vehicle verocity in Level A data element.
Note:
It is deemed as satisfaction if d) and e) can be obtained by other publicly available means (such as maintenance manual or official website).
Implementation Date For vehicle type applying for new type approval, all requirements except for Level B data elements <Paragraph_4.4
> specified in this standard shall be implemented from 01_January_2021; all requirements shall be implemented from 01_January_2023.

Vehicle types granted with type approval before 1_January_2021 are only required from 1_January_2021 for recording some data elements in this standard, including longitudinal delta-V, maximum recorded longtidudinal delta-V, time to achieve maximum delta-V (longitudinal), driving brake on/off (or brake pedal position), vehicle velocity and VIN.

If longitudinal acceleration is recorded, longitudinal delta-V, maximum recorded longitudinal delta-V and time to achieve maximum delta-V (longitudinal) might not be recored, and vehicle is required to be verified by either test in impact (5.1), driving operative data test (5.2), bench test (5.3) for validity.
Others are not required.
